description:
&lt;p&gt;We have an exciting opportunity for Clerical Officer to join our busy Outpatient Department.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will need to be a dynamic, flexible and highly motivated person with a professional attitude to join the Outpatient Team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will be required to provide a professional, efficient and comprehensive reception service within the main outpatient department. Using an advance level of computer skills, they will navigate Patient Administration Systems, perform data input and take an active role in departmental audits.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role requires the ability to work under own initiative and under pressure, demonstrating the ability to multitask. The role requires close liaison with other disciplines and the provision of a courteous, reliable and high quality service to patients, relatives and carers, healthcare professionals, internal departments and outside organisations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For further information please contact Matron Issie MACNIVEN at issie.macniven@nhs.net&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;**This job advert will close as soon as a sufficient amount of applications have been received. Please apply for this job as soon as you can, if you are interested.**&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
